lead_paragraph: Yamaha's triple MotoGP world champion Jorge Lorenzo won a crash-strewn French Grand Prix from pole position on Sunday to wrest the overall lead from fellow-Spaniard Marc Marquez after the Honda rider slid out.

headline.print_headline: Lorenzo Wins in France to Take Over From Marquez
headline.main: Lorenzo Wins in France to Take Over From Marquez
